The paper discusses a technique for calculating geodesics in semantic networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database (cs.DB) applications. The paper also mentions various network metrics, which are often studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the Resource Description Framework (RDF), which is a common format for representing semantic networks and is often used in natural language processing (cs.CL) applications.
